ing heat stress to your garden. These come with an internal reflector.</p></article><article class="module column product"><h1>Cool tube external reflector</h1><img src="images/content/coolexternal.jpg" alt=""><dl><dt>Available in</dt><dd>150mmx500mm, 150mmx600mm</dd></dl><p>These Cool Tubes are ideal for use in extremely hot conditions and for controlled CO2 environments. The heat created by the lights is contained in the tube and is channeled out through the duct. This means it is possible to run your lights much closer than regular HID lighting without burning or causing heat stress to your garden. These come with an external reflector.</p></article><article class="module column product"><h1>1000W Magnetic Ballast</h1><img src="images/content/magballast.jpg" alt=""><dl><dt>Maker</dt><dd>Growlush</dd></dl><p>Essential to fire your HID lamps.</p></article><article class="module column product"><h1>600W Electronic Dimmable Ballast</h1><img src="images/content/dimmable.jpg" alt=""><dl><dt>Maker</dt><dd>Powerplant</dd></dl><p>The PowerPlant Digital Ballast is one of the Best on the market today. Compatible with Both HPS and MH lamps these powerful ballasts have: Four level dimmable function, Super Lumen, 100%, 75% & 50%.</p></article><article class="module column product"><h1>Lucagrow HPS 1000w Lamp</h1><img src="images/content/lucagrow.jpg" alt=""><dl><dt>Maker</dt><dd>GE Lighting</dd></dl><p>The G.E Lucagrow HPS 1000W lamp offers a complete natural light substitute. With a long life of up to 28,500 hours, the lucagrow high output lamps give up to 20% more light than standard high pressure sodium lamps. The Lucagrow lamp maintains 90% light output over the life of the lamp and is fully interchangeable with other HPS lamps. The 1000W Lucagrow lamp will put out 140,000 lumens with a colour temperature of 2,100K.</p></article>